text.__SUMMARY__: Ulmus parvifolia var. coreana, the Korean elm, is a variety of the Chinese elm Ulmus parvifolia, native to Korea.
text.Cultivation: The tree is very rare in cultivation in the United States and Europe. There are no known cultivars of this taxon, nor is it known to be in commerce.
